  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Make-Up Artist Cum Manager, Bridal Studio",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Make-Up &amp; Styling:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provide professional bridal, pre-wedding, and event make-up and hairstyling services tailored to each client’s needs.</li>\n  <li>Stay updated with the latest beauty trends, techniques, and products.</li>\n  <li>Ensure high-quality standards and consistency across all beauty services.</li>\n  <li>Conduct trials and consultations with brides to finalize their desired look.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Team Management:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead, train, and mentor junior make-up artists and stylists.</li>\n  <li>Schedule and allocate assignments for make-up artists during shoots, weddings, and events.</li>\n  <li>Monitor team performance, providing feedback and support to maintain excellence.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Studio Operations &amp; Client Service:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage daily studio operations to ensure smooth workflow.</li>\n  <li>Handle client inquiries, bookings, and appointments with professionalism.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with bridal consultants, photographers, and gown specialists to ensure a seamless client experience.</li>\n  <li>Oversee stock management for cosmetics, tools, and skincare products.</li>\n  <li>Maintain studio hygiene and compliance with health and safety standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Administrative &amp; Business Support:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist management in planning promotions, packages, and collaborations.</li>\n  <li>Track and report studio performance, including client feedback and service quality.</li>\n  <li>Support in marketing initiatives such as social media content, bridal campaigns, and styled shoots.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Proven experience (20+ years) as a professional make-up artist, with strong bridal portfolio.</li>\n  <li>Previous experience in a supervisory or managerial role in the beauty/bridal industry.</li>\n  <li>Excellent knowledge of make-up techniques, products, and tools.</li>\n  <li>Strong leadership, communication, and organizational skills.</li>\n  <li>Ability to work under pressure, especially during peak wedding seasons.</li>\n  <li>Passionate, client-focused, and detail-oriented.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 20,
